cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about fine-tuning neural networks for domain adaptation in part of speech tagging. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of pre-trained units and the proposed method of augmenting the target-network with normalised, weighted and randomly initialised units are related to machine learning techniques, which fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the adaptation of pre-trained units to new domains, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks and the proposed method of augmenting the target-network can be related to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as well.
